# Turnitout Environment Configuration Template
# Copy this file to '.env' in the project root directory (adjacent to run.py).
# It allows adjusting the pipeline's behavior without editing configurations or code.

# ==============================================================================
# 1. SYNONYM AGGRESSIVENESS (TURNITOUT_AGGRESSIVENESS)
# ==============================================================================
# Controls the probability that a prose word will be replaced by a synonym
# from the rules dictionary.
#
# How to adjust:
#   - Set higher (e.g., 0.85 to 0.95) for maximum similarity reduction.
#     Note: Very high values may occasionally sound slightly less natural.
#   - Set lower (e.g., 0.40 to 0.60) to keep more of the original text's flow
#     while still disrupting long matching n-gram chains.
#   - Value must be a decimal (float) between 0.0 (0% swaps) and 1.0 (100% swaps).
# Default: 0.75
TURNITOUT_AGGRESSIVENESS=0.75

# ==============================================================================
# 2. MINIMUM SENTENCE LENGTH FOR CITATION (TURNITOUT_MIN_SENTENCE_LEN)
# ==============================================================================
# Sets the threshold (in characters) for a sentence to qualify for an appended 
# bibliography citation (\cite{...}) when scientific keywords are matched.
#
# How to adjust:
#   - Set higher (e.g., 60 to 80 characters) to ensure only long, complex
#     academic sentences receive citations, keeping headers and short statements
#     uncluttered.
#   - Set lower (e.g., 30 to 40 characters) if the document has short sentences
#     and more citation density is needed to satisfy similarity constraints.
# Default: 45
TURNITOUT_MIN_SENTENCE_LEN=45

# ==============================================================================
# 3. REPRODUCIBILITY SEED (TURNITOUT_RANDOM_SEED)
# ==============================================================================
# Seed value used to initialize the random number generator. 
#
# How to adjust:
#   - Keep the same (e.g., 42) to guarantee that running the tool on the same
#     input file yields the exact same synonym replacements and formatting outputs.
#   - Change to any other integer (e.g., 100, 777) to produce a different random
#     permutation of synonym choices for the same document.
# Default: 42
TURNITOUT_RANDOM_SEED=42
